The paper discusses the modeling of social storage systems as endogenous social networks and the study of their stability, efficiency, and contentedness. This falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses game theory to analyze the strategic network formation, which falls under the sub-category of game theory and economics (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the necessary and sufficient conditions for bilateral stability, which falls under the sub-category of network science (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the evolution of stable networks and ways to build contented networks, which falls under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computers and society (cs.CY), respectively.
